<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[524,677,1017,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hesychotypa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[524,677,1017,1041]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Hesychotypa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 24 described species widely distributed in the Neotropical region (
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A." box="[283,435,1050,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref9305" refString="Monne, M. A. 2018. Catalogue of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of the Neotropical Region. Part II. Subfamily Lamiinae. Available from http: // cerambyxcat. com /. (Last accessed December 2018.)" type="url" year="2018">Monné 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tavakilian, G. L. &amp; H. Chevillotte" box="[446,840,1050,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref9949" refString="Tavakilian, G. L., and H. Chevillotte. 2018. Base de Donnees Titan sur les Cerambycidae Mondiaux. Available at http: // titan. gbif. fr /. (Last accessed December 2018.)" type="url" year="2018">Tavakilian and Chevillotte 2018</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Dillon, L. S. &amp; E. S. Dillon" box="[1015,1309,1049,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 186" refId="ref9221" refString="Dillon, L. S., and E. S. Dillon. 1945. The tribe Onciderini (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) Part I. Reading Public Museum and Art Gallery, Scientific Publications 5: 1 - 186." type="journal article" year="1945">Dillon and Dillon (1945)</bibRefCitation>
: “The chief distinguishing characteristics of the genus are as follows: the elytra simply punctate, not granulate at base; antennae with third segment much longer than scape, moderately sinuate, scape short, robust, clavate; mesosternal process angulate each side, apex emarginated; humeri only slightly prominent, anterior margin strongly arcuate; head and pronotum always with alternate dark and pale vittae.”
</paragraph>
